Write a program to check a given number is an Armstrong Number or not, and return a suitable message.

Explanation:-
Armstrong number if the sum of its own digits raised to a power of digits results in the number itself..
Return Result: If the sum is equal to the original number, then the number is an Armstrong number; otherwise, it is not

1.        Example 1: Number 153
•        Calculation: 1^3+5^3+3^3=1+125+27=153
•        Result: 153 is an Armstrong number.

2.        Example 2: Number 371
•        Calculation: 3^3+7^3+1^3=27+343+1=371
•        Result: 371 is an Armstrong number.
